<subSubSection pageId="166" pageNumber="167" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="166.[151,1437,1436,1643]" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">
This family of tropical acalyptrate flies contains just over 100 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T." box="[959,1227,1472,1499]" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" refId="ref350035" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T. (2020) Systema Dipterorum. Version 2. 7. Available from: http: // www. diptera. org / (accessed 30 August 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Evenhuis &amp; Pape 2020</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[1247,1432,1472,1498]" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" pagination="63 - 112" refId="ref368107" refString="Rondani, C. (1848 b) Esame di varie specie d'insetti ditteri brasiliani. Studi Entomologici, 1 (1), 63 - 112, pl. IIIbis." type="journal article" year="1848">
Rondani (1848 
<bibRefCitation author="Robineau-Desvoidy, J. B." box="[1417,1432,1472,1498]" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" refId="ref365947" refString="Robineau-Desvoidy, J. B. (1863) Histoire naturelle des dipteres des environs de Paris. Tome second. Masson et Fils, Paris, 990 pp." type="book" year="1863">b</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, 1863) described one from South America and one without any indication of the 
<typeStatus box="[1044,1092,1509,1535]" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">type</typeStatus>
locality. The former is considered as a doubtful species (A. Pereira Colavite, pers. comm., 
<date box="[841,1008,1544,1570]" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" value="2013-02">February 2013</date>
) the latter as a valid species (
<bibRefCitation author="Steyskal, G. C." pageId="166" pageNumber="167" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref375254" refString="Steyskal, G. C. (1968 b) Family Neriidae. In: Papavero, N. (Ed.), A catalogue of the Diptera of the Americas south of the United States. Departamento de Zoologia, Secretaria de Agricultura, Sao Paulo, 49, 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1968">Steyskal 1968b</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[295,343,1581,1607]" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">type</typeStatus>
material of the species with no locality has presumably been lost; the South American 
<typeStatus box="[1317,1365,1581,1607]" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">type</typeStatus>
material is in the MZUN.
</paragraph>
